Package: exactplot
Title: Export ggplot2 Figures with Exact Plot-Area Dimensions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Quentin", "Rodriguez", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "quentin@example.com")
Description: Provides functions to export ggplot2 figures where the specified
    width and height refer to the actual plotting area (the panel region
    bounded by the axes), not the full device including margins, axis labels,
    titles, and legends. Supports multiple unit systems (cm, in, mm, pt) and
    allows precise control via coordinate-based specifications. The package
    uses a two-pass rendering strategy: it first builds the plot to measure
    non-panel grobs, then inflates the device dimensions so the panel ends
    up at exactly the requested size.
